  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2022-04-18",
    "date": "2022-07-29T19:50:34Z",
    "text": "Help for Healing Communities Act\n\nThis bill establishes a program through which the Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration may award grants to support mental and behavioral health services for survivors of active shooter events and incidents of targeted violence. Eligible grant recipients include state, tribal, territorial, and local governments and nonprofits located in or serving a community that experienced an active shooter event or incident of targeted violence in the preceding fiscal year."
